                        </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "a4">
                        <desc>
                          <locus target = "#iir"/> What seems to be birth (or death) record of an unidentified person
                        </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "a5">
                        <desc>
                          <locus target = "#8r"/> The year in which some one was ordained priest, <date calendar="ethiopian" when="1914" when-custom="1921/22" evidence="internal">በ፲፻፡ ወ፱፻፡ ፲ወ፬፡ አመተ፡ ምሕረት፡</date>
                        </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "a6">
                        <desc>
                          <locus target = "#167r"/><term key = "Asmat"/> prayers whose purpose is not clear, in a crude hand
                        </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "a7">
                        <desc>
                          The name <foreign xml:lang = "gez">መርጌታ፡ ገብረ፡ ማርያም፡</foreign>, <locus target = "#iv"/>
                        </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "a8">
                        <desc>
                          <locus target = "#66r"/> A small black cross above a text circled in black and red ink mark the midpoint of the Psalms
                        </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id = "a9">
                          <desc>
                            <locus target = "#167v"/> Illegible words, erased
                          </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id = "a10">
                          <desc>
                            Overlooked words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target = "#122r #151v #160r"/>);
                            and overlooked lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target = "#61r #81v #92v #93r #96r #98r #150r"/>).
                          </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id = "e1">
                          <desc>
                            The scribe’s chosen aspect ratio for the codex combined with the script size forces the scribe to reduce the font size
                            at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto the next line throughout the codex
                            (e.g., <locus target = "#1r #3r #6r #7v #10v"/>) But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes the
                            line of text above the end of the line (<locus target = "#2v #3v #5v #6v #7r #8r"/>, etc.) or below the end of the line
                            (<locus target = "#15r #73v #76v #107r"/>)
                          </desc>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                  </additions>
